<h1 class="topictitle1">Adding an Alarm Rule</h1>
<ol id="elb_ug_jk_0003__ol33525069103051"><li id="elb_ug_jk_0003__li104941610595">Log in to the management console.</li><li id="elb_ug_jk_0003__li21013674103051">Under <strong id="elb_ug_jk_0003__b191073314432">Management &amp; Deployment</strong>, click <strong id="elb_ug_jk_0003__b1644615466437">Cloud Eye</strong>.</li><li id="elb_ug_jk_0003__li60664407103051">In the navigation pane on the left, choose <strong id="elb_ug_jk_0003__b37954625102441">Alarm Management</strong> &gt; <strong id="elb_ug_jk_0003__b27549711102446">Alarm Rules</strong>.</li><li id="elb_ug_jk_0003__li35660604103051">On the <strong id="elb_ug_jk_0003__b84235270692348">Alarm Rules</strong> page, click <strong id="elb_ug_jk_0003__b84235270692351">Create Alarm Rule</strong>.The following describes how to create an alarm rule for a load balancer.<ol type="a" id="elb_ug_jk_0003__ol2089183717174"><li id="elb_ug_jk_0003__li1089237181715">Select <strong id="elb_ug_jk_0003__b171867139143426">Elastic Load Balancing</strong> for <strong id="elb_ug_jk_0003__b842352706143435">Resource Type</strong>.</li><li id="elb_ug_jk_0003__li118933731710">For <strong id="elb_ug_jk_0003__b148014231106">Dimension</strong>, select <strong id="elb_ug_jk_0003__b64825236015">Elastic Load Balancers</strong>. In the following operations, a load balancer is used as an example.</li><li id="elb_ug_jk_0003__li551885192811">Set other parameters as required and then click <strong id="elb_ug_jk_0003__b842352706144936">Create</strong>.<p id="elb_ug_jk_0003__p105181451182815">Once the alarm rule is set and you have enabled the notification function, the system automatically sends you a notification when an alarm is generated.</p>
<img src="public_sys-resources/note_3.0-en-us.png"><span class="notetitle"> </span><p id="elb_ug_jk_0003__p16126171111330">For more information about alarm rules of load balancers and listeners, see the <em id="elb_ug_jk_0003__i1655135817222">Cloud Eye User Guide</em>.</p>

</li></ol>

